## ARCHITECTURE.md as requirements authority

Before coding, read the scoped `ARCHITECTURE.md` and extract:

| Section | Use for |
| --- | --- |
| **Definition** | Page title, module purpose, audit object naming |
| **Includes** | In-scope entities, workflows, surfaces to build |
| **Does Not Include** | Hard boundaries — do not implement excluded domains; integrate via public doors only |
| **Requirement Statement** | One-paragraph scope check |
| **Enterprise Functional Requirements** (`HRM-XXX-NNN`) | Phase planning, contract tests, audit coverage |
| **Enterprise Acceptance Criteria** | Definition of done per phase |

**Verdict:**

```txt
MUST NOT implement rows under "Does Not Include" — reference owning module instead.
MUST map every mutation in phase to a requirement code in the final report.
MUST NOT mark acceptance criteria complete unless runtime behavior is verified.
MUST treat cross-module references (payroll, attendance, shift scheduling) as integration contracts, not duplicated engines.
```

