## Delivery phases (default ladder)

Adjust phase contents per `ARCHITECTURE.md`; this is the default sequencing for ERP HRM slices.

| Phase | Goal | Typical deliverables |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **0 — Clarify** (`PHASE_0_MODE: clarify`) | **Plan gate — no code** | Phase 0–4 map, entity model, boundary/integration table, route/permission proposal, pattern per surface, open questions, disk gap analysis |
| **0 — Foundation** (`PHASE_0_MODE: implement`) | Contracts + registry scaffold | `*.contract.ts`, Zod schema skeleton, audit strings, ERP permissions, `HRM_CAPABILITIES` + segment, directory scaffold, placeholder route |
| **1 — MVP core** | First shippable workflow | Schema + migrations if needed, core queries/mutations, primary surface (Pattern A/B), thin route or dedicated page, loading, permission gate, empty states |
| **2 — Operational depth** | Manager/employee workflows | Pattern C trailing actions, approval states, validation rules |
| **3 — Advanced workflow** | Multi-step / compliance / rich workflow | Pattern C queues or Pattern K where pipeline fits — not for simple approval inboxes |
| **4 — Integration + reporting** | Cross-module + reports | Read-only integration via `#features/hrm/server`; report surfaces; full audit coverage |

**Verdict:**

```txt
WHEN DELIVERY_PHASE=0 AND PHASE_0_MODE=clarify (default):
  MUST NOT write code, schema, migrations, or routes.
  MUST produce Phase 0 Clarification Report (see below).
  MAY ask up to 3 blocking questions; otherwise state assumptions explicitly.

WHEN DELIVERY_PHASE=0 AND PHASE_0_MODE=implement:
  Implement foundation artifacts only — no Phase 1 UI workflow unless user expands scope.

WHEN DELIVERY_PHASE≥1:
  Implement only that phase unless lower-phase artifacts are missing on disk.
```

### Workflow → UI pattern guide

| Domain shape | Pattern | Gold reference |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Config + master list (types, policies) | **A + B** | `leave-page.tsx` (sections), `salary-benchmarking-survey/` |
| Approval inbox (approve/reject/return) | **C** | `leave-pending-inbox.tsx` + `leave-decision-form` |
| Pipeline / stage columns | **K** | `claim-kanban-section.tsx`, `recruitment-pipeline-kanban-section.tsx` |
| Full multi-section workbench | **mixed** | `recruitment-page.tsx` |

Do **not** default to Kanban for approval workflows — use Pattern C unless columns represent durable pipeline stages.

