## Module directory shape (required)

Under `DEVELOPMENT_SCOPE`, follow Afenda module vocabulary:

```txt
actions/          → Server Actions ("use server")
data/             → server-only queries, mutations, *-surface-builders.server.ts, *-list-surface.server.ts
components/       → RSC pages/sections + *.client.tsx islands
schemas/          → Zod — safe for client import when shared
*.contract.ts     → audit action strings (buildCrudSapAuditAction)
ARCHITECTURE.md   → requirements authority (already present)
index.ts          → public door via #features/<module> (wire exports deliberately)
client.ts         → client-safe actions/types only
```

**Scaffold when starting Phase 0/1:**

```bash
pnpm gen audit-contract --module hrm --object <object> --verb create
pnpm gen action --module hrm --object <object> --verb create --tier B
```

Use `pnpm gen capability` only when creating a **new top-level ERP module** — HRM sub-slices usually nest under existing `#features/hrm`.

