## HRM wiring checklist (when MODULE=hrm)

When `ROUTE_SEGMENT` is not `none-yet`, complete in the **same phase** as the route:

1. [ ] Add segment to `lib/features/hrm/hrm-apps-path.shared.ts` (`HRM_APPS_CAPABILITY_SEGMENTS`)
2. [ ] Add row to `HRM_CAPABILITIES` in `lib/features/hrm/constants.ts` (audit prefix, nav, `requiredPermission`)
3. [ ] Add ERP permission keys via `#features/erp-rbac` (`buildErpPermissionKey` — object e.g. `flexible_work`, functions `search|read|create|update`)
4. [ ] **Phase 0 route option:** register segment only — `app/.../apps/hrm/[segment]/page.tsx` serves `HrmSegmentCapabilityRoutePage` → `HrmCapabilityPlaceholderPage` until dedicated page ships
5. [ ] **Phase 1+ route option:** dedicated thin `app/(main)/[locale]/o/[orgSlug]/apps/hrm/<segment>/page.tsx` + `loading.tsx` (overrides `[segment]` leaf)
6. [ ] Export page component from `#features/hrm` `index.ts`
7. [ ] i18n: `messages/en.json` under `Dashboard.Hrm.*` and `Dashboard.Hrm.cards.<segment>.*` for placeholder
8. [ ] `revalidatePath`: `toLocaleOrgAppsRevalidatePattern("/hrm/<segment>")` in actions
9. [ ] Update `tests/unit/hrm-contract.test.ts` (or equivalent) when touching `HRM_CAPABILITIES` / segment sets

**Route verdict:** `/{locale}/o/{orgSlug}/apps/hrm/{segment}` — never `/dashboard/hrm`.

